Welcome back to The Best & The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m Tara
Palmeri, wishing everyone in Los Angeles safety and good health. I ended up=
 on the Westside of the city for an extended trip and had to evacuate, like=
 many others, but unlike them I=E2=80=99m not leaving a home behind. I=E2=
=80=99m devastated for the people who have lost their homes and communities=
, and I=E2=80=99m keeping you all in my thoughts and prayers.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

In tonight=E2=80=99s issue, I dig into the topic that is keeping K
Street up at night: TikTok, the Chinese-owned company that has hired pretty=
 much anyone with proximity to power in the Biden White House or incoming T=
rump administration to lobby on their behalf. The platform is set to go dar=
k next week if the Supreme Court doesn=E2=80=99t grant Trump=E2=80=99s requ=
est for a stay of the law that would ban the app if it=E2=80=99s not sold=
=E2=80=94a petition he filed via amicus brief when confronted with the deva=
stating prospect that hundreds of
millions of viewers might miss his inauguration. One thing is for certain: =
Trump is now sold on the app he once called a national security threat and =
