;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0=
px;line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">While Washington braces for Inauguration D=
ay, when
<strong>Donald Trump </strong>will take the oath of office on the Capitol s=
teps, Trump himself has become fixated on the day <em>before</em>: January =
19, the deadline for TikTok to find a U.S. buyer or face a countrywide ban.=
 Trump, who previously led the charge to ban the app, himself, has recently=
 become enamored with the idea of saving it=E2=80=94preserving a platform t=
hat has developed a sizable MAGA-friendly audience and doing a solid for th=
e growing number of friends and allies who have an
economic interest in keeping TikTok alive. With the Supreme Court scheduled=
 to hear arguments on Friday regarding whether to overturn or delay the law=
=E2=80=94which provides the sitting president with the ability to institute=
 a 90-day freeze <em>if he=E2=80=99s in the process of facilitating a =E2=
=80=9Cqualified divestiture=E2=80=9D</em>=E2=80=94Trump perceives a golden =
opportunity to swoop in and consummate the ultimate deal.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px=
;">Just as
importantly, perhaps, postponing the TikTok ban would give Trump yet anothe=
r channel on which to simulcast his triumphant return. It=E2=80=99s a pitch=
 that TikTok executives and its lobbyists and emissaries=E2=80=94including =
Trump allies <strong>Kellyanne Conway</strong>,<strong> David Urban, Johnny=
 McEntee</strong>,<strong> Brian Ballard</strong>, and<strong> Charlie Kirk=
</strong>=E2=80=94have made directly and explicitly to the president-elect =
in recent weeks. =E2=80=9CThey=E2=80=99re spoon-feeding this to Trump,=E2=
=80=9D
said a source involved in the lobbying effort. =E2=80=9CThey=E2=80=99re hig=
hlighting to him just how big TikTok is for him and his people, and how if =
TikTok is shut down on January 19, none of the views will be on the inaugur=
ation. That resonated with him.=E2=80=9D Among the suitors has been <strong=
>Shou Zi Chew</strong>, the C.E.O. of TikTok, who met with the president-el=
ect on December 16 bearing charts showing Trump=E2=80=99s popularity on the=
 app (=E2=80=9C36 billion total views of #trump,=E2=80=9D etcetera). Trump =
loved them so much that
he Truthed them.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</=
p><p style=3D"margin:0;">The pro-TikTok brigade has been appealing to Trump=
=E2=80=99s vanity in other ways, too. Trump and Chew spoke again by phone o=
n December 27, according to a source with knowledge of the call=E2=80=94the=
 same day Trump filed an amicus brief calling for a 90-day stay. According =
to the argument filed with the court, =E2=80=9CPresident Trump alone posses=
ses the consummate dealmaking expertise, the electoral mandate, and the
political will to negotiate a resolution to save the platform while address=
ing the national security concerns expressed by the Government.=E2=80=9D No=
tably, Trump=E2=80=99s attorney <strong>John Sauer</strong>=E2=80=94who als=
o argued his criminal immunity case before SCOTUS=E2=80=94didn=E2=80=99t re=
ally address the First Amendment question. Instead, he writes that the cour=
t should =E2=80=9Cstay the statute=E2=80=99s effective date=E2=80=9D to =E2=
=80=9Callow his incoming Administration to pursue a negotiated resolution.=
=E2=80=9D In other words: <em>I alone can fix it.</em>
</p></div>
