owner <strong>Frank McCourt</strong> and Mr. Wonderful, <strong>Kevin O=E2=
=80=99Leary</strong>=E2=80=94is that a group of American investors should b=
uy the company outright from ByteDance, with Trump=E2=80=99s backing, as pa=
rt of a
trade deal. Under this proposed solution, Trump would use the threat of tar=
iffs to pressure China to sell, an approach in line with Trump=E2=80=99s in=
ternational negotiating technique and already a subject of discussion with =
Trump=E2=80=99s nominee for treasury secretary, <strong>Scott Bessent</stro=
ng>. (Bessent, too, has met with Chew.) One source with knowledge of this t=
hinking described the advantage for Trump this way: =E2=80=9CTrump will say=
, =E2=80=98I will help find an American buyer.=E2=80=99 He can be the hero =
and say he
helped an American find the money.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;m=
argin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Farfe=
tched? Maybe. President <strong>Xi Jinping</strong> faces his own domestic =
pressures not to be seen capitulating to a foreign rival, especially amid s=
luggish economic growth and a rising hypernationalist mood. But other U.S. =
trading partners including Canada and Mexico have already responded to Trum=
p=E2=80=99s tariff threats with performative gestures designed to
appease, distract, or offer up quick and cosmetic wins. A proponent of this=
 route who has knowledge of the discussions told me: =E2=80=9CThe chances o=
f China doing a deal was at 0 percent, and now we think it=E2=80=99s at 30 =
percent,=E2=80=9D in exchange for Trump offering =E2=80=9Cless punitive eco=
nomic agreements on tariffs.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Meanwhile, =
potential investors are trying to reach Trump through the press=E2=80=94whi=
ch explains why <em>Shark
Tank</em> co-host O=E2=80=99Leary was on Fox this week speaking directly to=
 the president-elect. =E2=80=9CTrump will be who we have to work with to cl=
ose the deal in the months ahead,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CSo I wanted to=
 let him know, as well as others in his cabinet, that we=E2=80=99re doing t=
his, and we=E2=80=99re going to need their help.=E2=80=9D (The last time O=
=E2=80=99Leary was at Mar-a-Lago, he was talking up the fantasy of making C=
anada the 51st state.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Today,
McCourt and O=E2=80=99Leary announced =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://email.puc=
k.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVVG52S245Q0xtTHRBNGlD=
YU1ocz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlcGVvcGxlc2JpZC5jb20vP3V0bV9jYW1wYWl=
nbj1UaGUrQmVzdCslMjYrVGhlK0JyaWdodGVzdCstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkY5JTJGMj=
UlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1UaGUrQmVzdCslMjYrVGhlK0JyaWdodGVzdCstK1NVQlNDU=
klCRVJTKyUyODElMkY3JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAy=
NnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmE=
iLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwMzg4NDl9/1ae21=
38a22eb7c25bdac6f64dfa455b459de90be9e86f57533913ccb9079193f" style=3D"text-=
decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">The People=E2=80=99s Bid for TikTok</a=
>,=E2=80=9D calling it a =E2=80=9Ca once-in-a-generation opportunity for Am=
ericans to reclaim a voice, choice, and stake in the future of the internet=
=2E=E2=80=9D McCourt has supposedly secure=
d about $20 billion in commitments=20=
from private equity, but at the end of the day, it=E2=80=99s unclear what t=
he platform is worth without its vaunted algorithm=E2=80=94the secret sauce=
 that has made
the app so addictive. And not all of McCourt and O=E2=80=99Leary=E2=80=99s =
peers think they are particularly serious contenders, even if the two men a=
re clearly serious about the bid, themselves. =E2=80=9CNo one in the incomi=
ng administration is talking to us about a sale,=E2=80=9D a source working =
for TikTok told me. =E2=80=9CThese billionaires who are going around saying=
 they are going to buy TikTok are nothing but peacockers and masqueraders.=
=E2=80=9D</p></div>
